        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>The target becomes distracted and suggestible, inundated by vivid daydreams.</p>\n<hr /><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected.\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target's attention wavers. It becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Flat-Footed]{Flat-Footed} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Fascinated]{Fascinated} by its daydreams.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> As success, except that you appear in the dream and give a suggestion. This can be to approach you, run away (as if it had the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Fleeing]{Fleeing} condition), Release what it's holding, Drop @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Prone]{Prone}, or stand in place. The creature follows this course of action as its first action after you Cast the Spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the target follows the course of action for as many actions as possible for the spell's duration, and it does nothing else.</p>"
        },
